              "messageEventInfo": "{}",
              "messageDisplayInfo": "{}"
            },
            "content": "Hello, Inderpreet, \n \n Sorry for the late reply. I have looked at the pictures and catalog you sent; children's pajama sets are a category that we have been working on consistently. \n \n To be honest, since this is a product from another factory, we don't have physical samples to accurately match the fabric weight and specific feel, and we cannot exactly replicate the pattern. However, if you need products of this category and quality, we can use our own fabrics and existing patterns to make children's pajamas of the same type and quality for you, and there is room for negotiation on the price. \n \n We have done OEM work for Pampers and Disney, so you can rest assured about the fabric and workmanship. If you're interested, I can first send you some of our existing children's pajama styles to look at, or you can buy a physical sample to use as a template. We can match the fabric, workmanship, and design, and the quality won't be any worse than theirs. \n \n Do you think we should first look at our styles, or should we send you a sample?"
